\lim_{n\to\infty}\left(1+\frac{\lambda}{n}\right)^n=e^\lambda
0\cdot \infty
\left(1+\frac{1}{n}\right)^\lambda = \left(1+\frac{\lambda}{n}\right)
n
y=\left(1+\frac \lambda n\right)^n
\ln y=n\ln\left(1+\frac \lambda n\right)=\frac{\ln\left(1+\frac \lambda n\right)}{\frac1n}
\lim_{n\to\infty}\ln y=\lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{\ln\left(1+\frac \lambda n\right)}{\frac1n}\text{ which is in the form } \frac00 
\lim_{n\to\infty}\ln y=\lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{-\frac \lambda {n^2}}{-\frac1{n^2}\left(1+\frac \lambda n\right)}=\lambda
\lim_{n\to\infty}\ln y=\lambda\iff \lim_{n\to\infty}=e^\lambda
n=\lambda t
\lim_{t\to\infty}\left(1+\frac{1}{t}\right)^{\lambda t}=\left(\lim_{t\to\infty}\left(1+\frac{1}{t}\right)^t\right)^\lambda=e^\lambda
e = \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(1+\frac 1 n\right)^n
e^\lambda = \lim_{n \to \infty}  \left(1+\frac 1 n\right)^{n \lambda} =\\ \lim_{n \to \infty} \left( \left(1+\frac 1 n\right)^\lambda\right)^{n}=\\ \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(1+\frac{\lambda}{n}+O\left(\frac{1}{n^2}\right)\right)^{n} 
e^y=\sum_{0\le r<\infty}\frac{y^r}{r!}
